learning_outcomes.en:
After the course, the students are expected:
- to know how physics describes nature;
- to observe problems of the phenomenal physics;
- to be possessed of analyse methods of phenomena;
- to analyse various phenomena on the qualitative level;
- to be able  to differentiate the physical and pseudophysical explanations of phenomena;
- to use the acquired knowledge and skills at school practice;
- to compose and report the reviews of the phenomenal physics.
